Steps:-   SSH Login Access by Using Ubuntu.

        1) Launch Instances in EC2.
        2) Name of instances:- sshubuntu
        3) AMI:- Ubuntu select.
        4) After that By default setting.
        5) Launch Instances --> Copy It's Public IP.
        6) Open Putty.
        7) Host name(IP):- Public IP Paste of our instances EC2.
        8) Category : Connection --> Open SSH --> Open Auth --> Credentials.
        9) Put Private key file for Authentication --> Browse It (newprivate).
       10) Select Private key --> Open --> Open.
       11) Login as: ubuntu.
       12) Enter. 
       13) SSH Login through our Ubuntu Software in Putty app.
       14) After that do aws configure Process.
